{TEXT -1 17 "2.  (8 points) A " }{TEXT 300 9 "geometric" }{TEXT -1 
153 " sequence is one in which the ratio between consecutive terms is \+
always the same.  In  such a sequence there is an identifiable non-zer
o first term, say " }{TEXT 301 1 "a" }{TEXT -1 32 ", and a fixed commo
n ratio, say " }{TEXT 302 1 "r" }{TEXT -1 48 ".  Then, the sequence ta
kes on the form \{a, ar, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "ar^2;" "6#*$%#arG\"\"#" }
